        <headline>Heat Advisory issued August 7 at 11:36AM CDT until August 8 at 8:00PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>* WHAT...For the Heat Advisory today, hot temperatures up to 107
expected. For the Heat Advisory on Friday, hot temperatures up to
107 expected.

* WHERE...Central and eastern Texas and Oklahoma Panhandles
including Palo Duro Canyon State Park.

* WHEN...For the first Heat Advisory, until 8 PM CDT this evening.
For the second Heat Advisory, from 1 PM to 8 PM CDT Friday.

* IMPACTS...Hot temperatures and high humidity may cause heat
illnesses.
</description>
        <instruction>Drink plenty of fluids, stay in an air-conditioned room, stay out of
the sun, and check up on relatives and neighbors.</instruction>
